Setup (Run within powershell):

(This setup is to get tfidf and word2vec working. Make sure to put the reuters21578 folder in the same directory as the python files. You can find the download here: https://kdd.ics.uci.edu/databases/reuters21578/reuters21578.html)

python -m venv venv

.\venv\Scripts\activate

pip install beautifulsoup4
pip install nltk
pip install scikit-learn
pip install numpy==1.23.5
pip install gensim==4.3.2
pip install tqdm
pip install torch
pip install rich
pip install transformers
pip install rank_bm25
pip install spacey
pip install fasttext


python

import nltk

nltk.download('all')

exit()

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TF-IDF:
python tfidf_runner.py

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Word2Vec:
python word2vec_runner.py

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Experimental Word2Vec:
(Model takes a long time to train and is not included within test scripts "comparison_runner.py" and "tests.py".)

python experimental_word2vec.py

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Transformer:
(Extra model to enhance the project scope and experiement.)

python extra_transformer.py

-> then enter your query 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

comparison_runner.py:
(Compares tfidf and word2vec models.)
python comparison_runner.py

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

tests.py
(Compares tfidf and word2vec models.)
python tests.py
